what is tolerance events at stanford what is tolerance facebook twitter email print add to calendar inter group conflicts are best resolved in ethical and interpersonal terms combatants on each side must transcend their conflict by recognizing and affirming publicly their common humanity and by unilaterally renouncing the principle of retributive justice to paraphrase anwar sadat whom bland cites as such a transcender peace is won not by signing agreements but by embracing enemies please join a short presentation and open discussion what is tolerance by byron bland senior consultant and lecturer at stanford university dinner is provided at the end of the program when thursday february 23 2012 6 00 pm approximate duration of 1 hour s where oak lounge east tresidder memorial union map audience general public tags lecture reading sponsor cultural interaction club contact aigerimk stanford edu permalink http events stanford edu events 310 31097 more info last modified february 22 2012
